===message:I agree with you.  Women did not have the options they have today.  I don't think they had as much responsibilities as they have today either.  For example, I live next door to a lady who is over 70.  She was talking to me the other day and said that her husband, who is now deceased, used to take care of all the bills.  She has her daughter balance her checkbook for her still today.  But, I also think that women put up with a lot more then then they do today.  Divorce was not as prevalent as it is today.
